---
import MainLayout from "../../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import Header from "../../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../../components/Footer.astro";
import Hero from "../../../components/Hero.astro";
import Section from "../../../components/Section.astro";
import Card from "../../../components/Card.astro";
import Button from "../../../components/Button.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="Common Myths - Quiet the Mind">
  <Header slot="header" />

  <Hero
    title="Debunking Common Myths âœ¨"
    subtitle="Let's separate fact from fiction about intrusive thoughts and mental health."
  />

  <Section
    title="Myth vs. Reality"
    subtitle="Understanding the truth can reduce shame and self-blame:"
  >
    <div class="space-y-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <Card
          title="MYTH: 'I must be crazy'"
          icon="âŒ"
          class="border-red-200 dark:border-red-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            Having intrusive thoughts means there's something seriously wrong with my mental health.
          </p>
        </Card>
        <Card
          title="REALITY: You're completely normal"
          icon="âœ…"
          class="border-green-200 dark:border-green-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            Studies show that 94% of people experience intrusive thoughts. They're a normal part of human cognition.
          </p>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <Card
          title="MYTH: 'Thoughts predict actions'"
          icon="âŒ"
          class="border-red-200 dark:border-red-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            Having violent or disturbing thoughts means I'm likely to act on them.
          </p>
        </Card>
        <Card
          title="REALITY: Thoughts â‰  Actions"
          icon="âœ…"
          class="border-green-200 dark:border-green-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            People with intrusive thoughts are actually LESS likely to act on them because they find them so distressing.
          </p>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <Card
          title="MYTH: 'I should control all thoughts'"
          icon="âŒ"
          class="border-red-200 dark:border-red-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            Healthy people can control what they think about all the time.
          </p>
        </Card>
        <Card
          title="REALITY: Thoughts are involuntary"
          icon="âœ…"
          class="border-green-200 dark:border-green-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            No one can control every thought. The human mind naturally generates thousands of thoughts daily.
          </p>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <Card
          title="MYTH: 'Ignoring them works'"
          icon="âŒ"
          class="border-red-200 dark:border-red-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            If I just ignore intrusive thoughts, they'll go away on their own.
          </p>
        </Card>
        <Card
          title="REALITY: Acceptance works better"
          icon="âœ…"
          class="border-green-200 dark:border-green-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            Trying to suppress thoughts often makes them stronger. Acknowledging them without judgment is more effective.
          </p>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <Card
          title="MYTH: 'They mean something deep'"
          icon="âŒ"
          class="border-red-200 dark:border-red-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            Intrusive thoughts reveal hidden desires or suppress true feelings.
          </p>
        </Card>
        <Card
          title="REALITY: They're just mental noise"
          icon="âœ…"
          class="border-green-200 dark:border-green-800"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm">
            Intrusive thoughts are random mental events, like background noise. They don't reveal anything meaningful about you.
          </p>
        </Card>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section
    title="The Truth About Recovery"
    bgColor="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50/50 to-purple-50/50 dark:from-blue-900/10 dark:to-purple-900/10"
    centerContent={true}
  >
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <Card
        title="Knowledge is Power"
        icon="ðŸ’¡"
        variant="minimal"
        class="text-center"
      >
        <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
          <p>
            Understanding these myths helps break the cycle of shame and fear that often makes intrusive thoughts worse.
          </p>
          <p>
            Recovery isn't about eliminating intrusive thoughts completely - it's about changing your relationship with them so they no longer control your life.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-6 flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center gap-4">
          <Button href="/topics/intrusive-thoughts/strategies" variant="primary">
            Learn Coping Strategies
          </Button>
          <Button href="/topics/intrusive-thoughts" variant="secondary">
            Back to Overview
          </Button>
        </div>
      </Card>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</MainLayout>